To install rpm packages:
    1. sudo alien rpmpackage.rpm // generates .deb package
    2. sudo dpkg -i rpmpackage.deb // to install the generated .deb
    3. Or in a single command: 
        sudo alien -i rpmpackage.rpm

install gdebi to install .deb files using GUI

install git:
    sudo apt install git
install nvm:
    curl -o- https://raw.githubusercontent.com/creationix/nvm/v0.33.8/install.sh | bash
install node:
    nvm install 9.8.0
install zsh:
    sudo apt install zsh
    sh -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/robbyrussell/oh-my-zsh/master/tools/install.sh)"

https://unix.stackexchange.com/a/3445/74788

https://github.com/zsh-users/zsh-syntax-highlighting/blob/master/INSTALL.md
https://github.com/zsh-users/zsh-autosuggestions

install powerlevel9k theme for zsh
    also add at the top of .zshrc file this line: 
        export TERM="xterm-256color"

